📋 Requirements for Agent Workbench & Case Handling System
🧩 1. Functional Requirements (CORE FEATURES)
📌 Case Management
System should allow agents to:
Create a Collection Case
View case details (360° view)
Update case status:
Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed
Set priority (Low / Medium / High)
Assign case type:
Delinquency / Dispute / Hardship
📝 Case Notes
Agents should:
Add notes to a case
View all notes (history)
Each note must store:
Author
Timestamp
Description
📅 Follow-Up Task Management
System should:
Create tasks for a case
Assign tasks to agents
Track due dates
Mark status:
Open / Done / Overdue
⚠️ Hardship Handling
System should:
Flag accounts with hardship
Capture reason:
Medical / Job Loss / Natural Calamity
Track start & end date
Update hardship status
🔍 Case Search & Filters
Filter by:
Status
Priority
Case type
Assigned agent
Search by:
Case ID
Loan Account ID
📊 Dashboard (Important for your project)
Show:
Total cases
Open vs Closed
Overdue tasks
High priority cases
🔐 2. Security Requirements
User authentication (Login)
Role-based access control (RBAC):
ADMIN
AGENT
SUPERVISOR
Only authorized users can:
Create/update cases
Assign tasks
⚡ 3. Non-Functional Requirements
🚀 Performance
APIs should respond within < 2 seconds
🔄 Scalability
System should handle:
Multiple agents
Thousands of cases
🔒 Security
Use:
JWT Authentication
Encrypted passwords
📈 Availability
System should be available 24/7
🗄️ 4. Database Requirements
Use MySQL
Tables:
collection_case
case_note
follow_up_task
hardship_flag
user (for login)
🌐 5. API Requirements
Case APIs
POST /cases
GET /cases
GET /cases/{id}
PUT /cases/{id}
Notes APIs
POST /notes
GET /cases/{id}/notes
Task APIs
POST /tasks
GET /tasks
PUT /tasks/{id}
